{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"484b96d9-b7aa-4b56-a157-3d16e68131fb","content":"Here's how to migrate from `VSTest@3` to Microsoft.Testing.Platform while keeping TRX reports and code coverage:\n\n**1. Update your test projects** — add to each `.csproj`:\n```xml\n<EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n<OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n```\n\n**2. Replace the `VSTest@3` task** with `DotNetCoreCLI@2`:\n```yaml\n- task: DotNetCoreCLI@2\n  displayName: 'Run Tests'\n  inputs:\n    command: test\n    projects: '**/*Tests.csproj'\n    arguments: >-\n      --configuration $(BuildConfiguration)\n      --logger \"trx;LogFileName=TestResults.trx\"\n      --results-directory $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n      --collect \"Code Coverage\"\n```\n\n**3. Publish results & coverage:**\n```yaml\n- task: PublishTestResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish Test Results'\n  inputs:\n    testResultsFormat: VSTest\n    testResultsFiles: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.trx'\n  condition: always()\n\n- task: PublishCodeCoverageResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish Code Coverage'\n  inputs:\n    summaryFileLocation: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.cobertura.xml'\n```\n\n> For Cobertura output, add the `coverlet.collector` NuGet package and pass `--collect \"XPlat Code Coverage\"` instead, or use `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=Cobertura\"` with the Microsoft collector.\n\nKey differences from `VSTest@3`: tests are now self-hosted executables invoked via `dotnet test`, and result/coverage publishing is handled by separate tasks.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"89ebf343-1537-46b5-bd91-5d36ae9a9a01","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The repository doesn't seem to have relevant files. This is a general knowledge question about migrating from VSTest@3 to Microsoft.Testing.Platform in Azure DevOps pipelines. Let me provide guidance based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":501,"requestId":"CFE3:1605AB:6083C6C:6BB6C8F:69EC0EF3"},"id":"e92e9778-ec25-4bc8-b26b-e06f8ed55fab","timestamp":"2026-04-25T00:46:53.395Z","parentId":"5fb689d8-6098-4bd7-a798-ada05a0f4534"}
